title: Riverside Cyclo-cross Festival
description: The Riverside Cyclocross Festival takes place in the beautiful E. H. Young Riverfront Park.  This will be the 7th year of our event.  We will be hosting rounds 2 and 3 of the Kansas City Cross series.
course: Course is 1.5 miles long and includes a rocky staircase climb, sand pit, off-camber turns, short run-ups, plenty of pavement sections and a trip down to the Missouri River and back.
registration: Registration closes 15 minutes before each race.  Racing license must be shown at registration.  A one day license may be purchased for 10.00.
notes:
USCF permit applied for.
All USCF Cyclocross rules apply.
ANSI approved helmets required for all events.
Mountain bikes are allowed, but must have bar ends removed.
Races held rain or shine
A domestic USCF or NORBA license is required.
Parking: Follow signs to parking.
directions: From Kansas City: take I-29 North to I-635, merge onto US-69 South.  Turn left onto NW Frontage Rd., NW Frontage Rd becomes NW Tremont.  Turn right onto NW Argosy Parkway.  Follow signs to E.H. Young Riverfront Park.
